javax.jaxtx.model.jta.opt
Interface XAResource

public interface XAResource

The JTA participant side of the protocol. Required to interface to backend javax.transaction.xa.XAResource instances. XAResource interface is a Java mapping of the industry standard XA resource manager interface. Please refer to: X/Open CAE Specification Distributed Transaction Processing: The XA Specification, X/Open Document No. XO/CAE/91/300 or ISBN 1 872630 24 3.

commit

public void commit(javax.transaction.xa.Xid tranID,
                   boolean onePhase)
            throws javax.transaction.xa.XAException,
                   SystemException
Commit the global transaction specified.
Parameters:
tranID - the global transaction identifier.
onePhase - used to indicate whether the resource manager should use a one-phase commit optimisation. Not to be recommended if more than one resource is involved in the same transaction!
Throws:
javax.transaction.xa.XAException - Thrown by the resource manager to inform the transaction manager of an error encountered during transaction processing.
SystemException - Thrown to indicate that an unexpected error occurred.
